# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .gitignore — Business Challenge II (UHI Prediction)
#
# PUSH these:
#   - 5 FINAL notebooks
#   - README.md, requirements.txt, setup/
#   - Data/sample_*.csv (labels), Data/validation_dataset.csv (coords)
#   - Data/Predicted_*.csv (all predictions — final + experimental)
#   - Data/Freetown_training_from_predictions.csv (derived labels)
#   - Data/cache/ (building density + LST caches — small, skips slow steps)
#   - Data/Sierra Leone Building Footprints/ (~36 MB — under GitHub limit)
#   - _scene_cache/ (STAC pickles), city_data.pkl
#
# EXCLUDE these (too large or not needed):
#   - All TIFFs (>100 MB each — use setup/download_data.py from Drive)
#   - Chile / Brazil building footprint folders (>100 MB shapefiles)
#   - Building_Footprint_Data.zip (184 MB)
#   - Old experimental / backup notebooks
#   - Rio_Report/, logs, PNG exports, Python caches
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ── Python / OS / IDE ─────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[codz]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
.venv/
env/
venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp


# ── Experimental / backup / obsolete notebooks ────────────────────
*BACKUP*.ipynb
*PRE_*.ipynb
*FIXED_COPY*.ipynb
*_executed.ipynb
Challenge_Notebook_01_*.ipynb
Challenge Notebook  02 - Sample*.ipynb
Challenge Notebook 03 - Data Preparation*.ipynb
Model Comparison*.ipynb
Starter Notebook*.ipynb

# Keep the 5 FINAL notebooks
!FINAL - *.ipynb


# ── Report / run artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────
Rio_Report/
Rio_executed.ipynb
Rio_Report_run.log
_run_*.py
_apply_*.py
_fix_*.py
_add_*.py
_patch_*.py
_comprehensive_*.py
_batch_output.py
_boost_high.py
_make_*.py
_reapply_*.py


# ── Large satellite imagery (download via setup/download_data.py) ─
S2_median_*.tiff
sample_*.tiff
test_*.tiff
tiff_backup*/


# ── Large building footprint data (download separately) ───────────
# The ZIP (184 MB) exceeds GitHub's 100 MB file limit.
# Chile and Brazil extracted folders contain .shp files over 100 MB.
# Sierra Leone folder (~36 MB) IS committed — see below.
Data/Building_Footprint_Data.zip
Data/Chile Building Footprints/
Data/Brazil Building Footprints/
Data/__MACOSX/

# Explicitly keep Sierra Leone shapefiles (under size limit)
!Data/Sierra Leone Building Footprints/
!Data/Sierra Leone Building Footprints/**


# ── Root-level PNG exports (notebook-generated visuals) ───────────
output*.png
/*.png

# Allow docs images if we add them later
!docs/*.png


# ── Root-level experimental CSV outputs (non-Data/) ───────────────
/Predicted_Freetown_AdvancedModel.csv
/Predicted_Freetown_BaseModel.csv


# ── Misc ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.tmp
Rio_Report_run.log
